        <p>Converts the cursor to <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">Bubble</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">Callout</MadCap:conditionalText> mode, which lets you create a callout by clicking in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> and dragging a rectangle area. When you release the cursor, a "bubble" shape is created, which consists of a rectangular or square area for holding text and a pointy area for pointing toward an area of the image that you want to explain or emphasize. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Interface/UI_Elements/Bubble_Properties_Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="" MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">Bubble Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Interface/UI_Elements/Object_Properties_Window_Pane.htm#CalloutObjectProperties" MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">Callout Properties</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
